      {
        "fromFrame": 549,
        "durationInFrames": 267,
        "background": "radial-gradient(ellipse 90% 60% at 50% -10%, rgba(99, 102, 241, 0.06) 0%, transparent 60%), linear-gradient(180deg, #0a0a0c 0%, #08080a 100%)",
        "layoutPreset": "code_and_callouts",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "code",
            "content": "```python\nfor node in graph:\n    distance[node] = unknown\n\ndistance[start] = 0\nqueue.push(start, cost=0)\n\nwhile queue is not empty:\n    node = queue.pop_cheapest()\n    if node is visited:\n        continue\n\n    mark node as visited\n    for neighbor, road_cost in graph[node]:\n        new_cost = distance[node] + road_cost\n        if new_cost < distance[neighbor]:\n            distance[neighbor] = new_cost\n            queue.push(neighbor, new_cost)\n```",
            "iconName": null,
            "width": null,
            "height": null,
            "x": 110,
            "y": 236,
            "animation": "fade"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "The whole loop\n\nA priority queue keeps the next cheapest node at the front, so the algorithm does not scan every node each time.\n\n- A priority queue keeps the next cheapest node at the front\n- so the algorithm does not scan every node each time.",
            "iconName": "Workflow",
